01:13.380 --> 01:15.380
Mary. Hey!
Wh-where you been?

01:15.382 --> 01:17.082
Oh, hey, Jack.

01:17.084 --> 01:18.750
Everything good?
Nice to see you.

01:18.752 --> 01:20.635
We're making real
progress knocking down

01:20.637 --> 01:22.304
the affordable housing part
of the court order.

01:22.306 --> 01:24.923
- We-- we just need to keep the pressure on.
- Uh-huh.

01:24.925 --> 01:28.226
And the compromise plan
the council approved

01:28.228 --> 01:30.845
fell apart the day before they
were going to give it to Sand.

01:30.847 --> 01:34.266
Mary, we can stop
the next 800 units.

01:34.268 --> 01:36.434
Jack, the thing is

01:36.436 --> 01:39.654
affordable housing is for
people who can afford to rent.

01:39.656 --> 01:41.156
So it's not
the same thing.

01:41.158 --> 01:42.607
It's the same.

01:42.609 --> 01:45.160
It drops down property values,
it brings in the bad element.

01:45.162 --> 01:48.163
It's just I don't
agree with you, okay?

01:48.165 --> 01:49.781
They said you went
to the other side.

01:49.783 --> 01:50.999
I didn't believe them.

01:51.001 --> 01:52.667
You working with the
housing people now, right?

01:52.669 --> 01:54.953
They tried the same
program in Greenburgh

01:54.955 --> 01:56.454
and it worked, Jack.

01:56.456 --> 01:58.840
Bullshit! You really think
it could make a difference?

01:58.842 --> 02:00.258
Yes, I do.

02:00.260 --> 02:02.627
- These people live like animals...
- Whoa.

02:02.629 --> 02:05.096
...and you're sitting around
singing "Kumbaya,"

02:05.098 --> 02:06.715
please don't put trash
on my street.

02:06.717 --> 02:08.300
Good luck with that, Mary.

02:08.301 --> 02:09.768
Jack, do you hear yourself?

02:16.310 --> 02:18.443
And tonight you'll hear
not only from me

02:18.445 --> 02:21.479
but representatives
of the police department,

02:21.481 --> 02:23.448
the sanitation
department,

02:23.450 --> 02:26.067
the Housing Authority
Maintenance Office.

02:26.069 --> 02:29.321
Cheapest bid for moving
costs came in at 700.

02:29.323 --> 02:31.323
<i>And HUD isn't willing</i>
<i>to pay for that,</i>

02:31.325 --> 02:33.575
so how many of you
can afford $350?

02:33.577 --> 02:35.877
Half the cost?

02:37.748 --> 02:40.048
And if you had six months
to pay for that?

02:40.050 --> 02:42.500
That would help?

02:42.502 --> 02:43.802
Yeah?

02:43.804 --> 02:45.470
Security deposits
may not be used

02:45.472 --> 02:48.006
to pay rent
or other charges

02:48.008 --> 02:50.725
while tenants are occupying
the dwelling units.

02:50.727 --> 02:52.894
A show of hands for those
of you who could afford

02:52.896 --> 02:56.097
a washer-dryer
stack unit at $500.

02:56.099 --> 02:58.733
If there is illegal activity
within any of the units,

02:58.735 --> 03:00.852
<i>you can expect</i>
<i>a zero-tolerance approach</i>

03:00.854 --> 03:02.354
to anything that
comes to our attention.

03:02.356 --> 03:06.024
In which case, a tenant found to
be involved in illegal activity

03:06.026 --> 03:07.492
will be evicted.

03:07.494 --> 03:08.993
How many of you
have lawn mowers?

03:08.995 --> 03:11.913
Any drug involvement
by any member of your family

03:11.915 --> 03:13.915
will result in
immediate expulsion.

03:13.917 --> 03:16.868
And with more trash that can fit
inside the in-ground receptacle,

03:16.870 --> 03:19.671
it should be double-bagged
and sealed like this.

03:22.592 --> 03:24.759
Any questions?

03:24.761 --> 03:26.344
And you will, at times,
encounter members

03:26.346 --> 03:27.796
of a neighborhood
watch group

03:27.798 --> 03:29.931
who will be
patrolling the area.

03:29.933 --> 03:31.266
And-- yes, ma'am?

03:31.268 --> 03:32.634
Will the white folks
have to learn

03:32.636 --> 03:34.269
how to be good
neighbors as well?

03:34.271 --> 03:35.937
- Excuse me?
<i>- Yeah, what you mean,</i>

03:35.939 --> 03:37.522
<i>"neighborhood watch</i>
<i>group"?</i>

03:37.524 --> 03:38.973
Who are they watching, me?

03:38.975 --> 03:42.477
Yeah. And are those
people attending a course

03:42.479 --> 03:43.945
so they can learn
how to accept us?

03:43.947 --> 03:46.781
Like we're taking this course
to learn how to accept them?

03:46.783 --> 03:48.199
Mm-hmm.

03:51.405 --> 03:52.787
<i>Right.</i>

03:57.744 --> 04:01.746
You started out thinking
you wanted to make a move,

04:01.748 --> 04:03.882
<i>to live somewhere better,</i>

04:03.884 --> 04:06.668
but is that still
what you want?

04:06.670 --> 04:09.888
Do you still want to move
into these new homes

04:09.890 --> 04:11.473
in this new neighborhood,

04:11.475 --> 04:13.558
<i>given what you've heard,</i>
<i>what you've seen,</i>

04:13.560 --> 04:15.643
and what we've gone over?

04:17.596 --> 04:20.732
Everything has a cost.

04:20.733 --> 04:25.103
Every choice
means responsibility.

04:26.656 --> 04:29.324
And it will be different.

04:29.326 --> 04:31.443
Different isn't
always better.

04:32.996 --> 04:36.114
But it does mean
"different."

04:38.418 --> 04:40.618
So...

04:40.620 --> 04:42.787
let me ask you...

04:42.789 --> 04:45.206
<i>did you come here</i>
<i>to make your life</i>

04:45.208 --> 04:49.260
and the lives
of your family different?

04:56.102 --> 04:57.602
- You didn't.
- Oh, yeah.

04:57.604 --> 04:59.270
Hey, man,
I'm a hardheaded Polack.

04:59.272 --> 05:02.223
You don't play ball with me,
I shove the bat up your ass.

05:02.225 --> 05:04.108
- Are you fucking crazy, Nick?
- You know what?

05:04.110 --> 05:06.945
Maybe Zakian wasn't so bad
on the Parking Authority.

05:06.947 --> 05:09.481
Maybe I made a mistake
corralling votes to replace him.

05:09.483 --> 05:11.733
- A guy can learn, can't he?
<i>- Yeah, I get it.</i>

05:11.735 --> 05:13.318
You want to frost
Zaleski's balls,

05:13.320 --> 05:17.455
but, Nick, you already publicly supported
replacing Zakian with Bob Jean.

05:17.457 --> 05:18.696
For you to flip now--

05:18.697 --> 05:21.460
Look, Vinni, I'm the minority
leader on the council,

05:21.461 --> 05:24.996
and I'm just opening up the lines
of communication with my mayor.

05:27.167 --> 05:28.716
Don't look at me, Vin.

05:28.718 --> 05:30.251
I'm a simpleminded
Republican

05:30.253 --> 05:32.670
without a dog anywhere
near this fight.

05:32.672 --> 05:34.672
But I would like to be
a fly on the wall

05:34.674 --> 05:36.424
when Zaleski
gets the news.

05:40.897 --> 05:43.014
<i>Still on the truck.</i>

05:43.016 --> 05:45.567
<i>- Jose.</i>
<i>- Yes, sir.</i>

05:45.569 --> 05:47.485
<i>It ain't there.</i>

05:47.487 --> 05:50.271
<i>No, the other box.</i>

05:55.495 --> 05:58.329
<i>Where's this go?</i>

05:58.331 --> 06:01.165
<i>I think she wants that</i>
<i>'round back.</i>

06:01.167 --> 06:04.252
<i>This is heavier
than I thought.</i>

06:04.254 --> 06:05.870
<i>- Screwdriver.</i>
<i>- It's in the truck.</i>

06:05.872 --> 06:07.872
- Go get it.
- All right, ma'am.

06:07.874 --> 06:09.340
Thank you.

06:14.381 --> 06:15.847
Ah!

06:15.849 --> 06:17.599
<i>This going inside?</i>

06:17.601 --> 06:19.133
- You gonna help me?
- Yeah.

06:19.135 --> 06:21.553
You gonna help me?

06:21.555 --> 06:23.104
Thank you, Johnny.

06:23.106 --> 06:25.189
Yeah, you hold that.
Right?

06:25.191 --> 06:28.560
Good Lord,
the junk you have.

06:28.562 --> 06:31.312
Daddy says he's giving you
the couch in the basement.

06:31.314 --> 06:32.947
He says not to argue.

06:35.118 --> 06:36.618
Have you seen Jaron?

06:39.122 --> 06:40.572
Jaron?

06:40.574 --> 06:42.040
Jaron!

06:54.588 --> 06:56.471
I-- in my room,
I have this window,

06:56.473 --> 06:58.640
and it looks out into, what,
like four, five trees--

06:58.642 --> 07:00.425
Mom, come see
the bedrooms.

07:00.427 --> 07:02.393
Yeah, do you want to
go see them?

07:02.395 --> 07:04.846
Yeah, we should get going.
Felipe.

07:06.099 --> 07:08.099
But you don't need
to leave yet...

07:10.437 --> 07:12.687
Roberto, come.
Time to go.

07:15.108 --> 07:16.858
<i>Maria.</i>

07:19.412 --> 07:20.612
Maria.

07:33.009 --> 07:36.377
- Bye,<i> mi chiquito.</i>
- Bye. Love you.

07:38.632 --> 07:41.132
It's a really
beautiful house.

07:41.134 --> 07:42.967
- <i> Gracias,</i> Carmen.
- Thank you,<i> Tia.</i>

07:44.354 --> 07:46.387
- 157?
- Yeah, 157.

07:46.389 --> 07:47.972
- You know what we forgot?
- What?

07:47.974 --> 07:50.141
- Okra.
- Oh, we'll never hear the end of it.

07:50.143 --> 07:51.476
You'll never hear
the end of it.

07:51.478 --> 07:52.727
Go home, niggers!

07:52.729 --> 07:55.947
Yeah, you, you goddamn
porch monkeys!

07:55.949 --> 07:57.482
<i>Damn it!</i>

08:01.538 --> 08:02.820
Go ahead.

08:09.329 --> 08:10.995
- The bottom shelf?
- Yeah.

08:10.997 --> 08:12.130
<i>Hey, Mama.</i>

08:12.132 --> 08:14.465
<i>Dwayne, is that you?</i>

08:15.552 --> 08:16.918
And Libby.

08:18.672 --> 08:20.505
We brought you and Tash
some groceries.

08:20.507 --> 08:21.923
- Oh.
- How you making out?

08:21.925 --> 08:23.841
I don't know.

08:23.843 --> 08:26.227
- It's gonna take some getting used to.
- Uh-huh.

08:27.397 --> 08:31.182
It's beautiful, Norma.
Just beautiful.

08:31.184 --> 08:33.267
- What y'all get us?
- Oh, uh, uh...

08:33.269 --> 08:34.902
- Nillas?
- Bam!

08:34.904 --> 08:37.105
- Okay.
- Oh, I can make myself banana pudding.

08:43.663 --> 08:46.030
Nick, did you
see this?

08:46.032 --> 08:48.449
You're quoted here
saying that I told you

08:48.451 --> 08:50.835
Bob Jean's
mismanaging the YPA.

08:50.837 --> 08:53.538
Yeah.
"Herald Statesman," right?

08:53.540 --> 08:56.207
I never fucking
said that.

08:56.209 --> 08:58.042
Yeah, I'm just
having a little fun.

08:58.044 --> 09:00.261
I'm bringing back John Zakian
to the Parking Authority.

09:00.263 --> 09:01.512
I'm gonna replace
Bob Jean.

09:01.514 --> 09:03.381
At my expense?

09:03.383 --> 09:05.099
It's okay.
I got the votes.

09:05.101 --> 09:07.552
I talked to Nick Spano,
and he's gonna get his guy to go for it,

09:07.554 --> 09:08.886
so that makes three.

09:08.888 --> 09:11.639
Nick, when you got rid of Zakian,
he was my boss,

09:11.641 --> 09:13.441
- but the mayor had your back.
- <i> Yeah?</i>

09:13.443 --> 09:15.777
So, now you're gonna
go against the mayor

09:15.779 --> 09:17.145
to try and fire
my new boss?

09:17.147 --> 09:18.863
Yeah.
You're gonna be fine.

09:18.865 --> 09:20.732
I got the votes.
I'm telling you, trust me.

09:20.734 --> 09:22.700
What is it that you're
trying to accomplish with this?

09:22.702 --> 09:24.452
- I'm just letting him know.
- Know what?

09:24.454 --> 09:26.204
That you have
some votes at the YPA?

09:26.206 --> 09:28.039
That I'm still here,
God damn it!

09:29.709 --> 09:31.409
I gave him
everything he has.

09:31.411 --> 09:34.295
I gave him-- I pushed
the housing through,

09:34.297 --> 09:37.582
I gave him the strong-mayor charter,
the patronage, the power.

09:37.584 --> 09:39.333
I stepped aside
to let him be mayor.

09:39.335 --> 09:42.170
I did all that,
and I paid for it, and I bled for it.

09:44.507 --> 09:46.007
<i>I'm not gonna</i>
<i>be ignored.</i>

09:46.009 --> 09:49.343
If Zaleski doesn't
wanna give me my due, that's fine.

09:49.345 --> 09:52.897
I'm just gonna make him look like
the jackass that he is.

09:52.899 --> 09:54.265
Nick.

09:55.985 --> 09:57.101
Just trust me.

10:44.984 --> 10:46.984
Where's Tasha?

10:46.986 --> 10:49.237
I think she went to bed
a while ago.

10:49.239 --> 10:51.956
<i>Yeah, you sure got
a lot of stuff here, Ma.</i>

10:51.958 --> 10:55.743
- Mm-hmm.
- The moving man did a job today, didn't he?

10:55.745 --> 10:57.161
Dwayne, honey,
I don't think

10:57.163 --> 10:59.330
I can keep my eyes
open much longer.

11:01.551 --> 11:03.501
I don't think
they're coming back.

11:03.503 --> 11:05.503
Who?

11:05.505 --> 11:07.505
Who not coming back?

11:07.507 --> 11:08.890
<i>No one, Ma.</i>

11:14.681 --> 11:16.981
When we were parking
the car out front,

11:16.983 --> 11:19.517
a couple of guys
drove past.

11:19.519 --> 11:21.352
Some words were said.

11:21.354 --> 11:22.687
What'd they say?

11:24.157 --> 11:26.858
What did they say?

11:31.781 --> 11:33.581
Oh.

11:33.583 --> 11:35.533
Libby's right,
Mama.

11:35.535 --> 11:37.118
They're gone.

11:37.120 --> 11:39.453
Well, of course
they gone.

11:39.455 --> 11:41.289
Y'all need
to be gone, too.

11:41.291 --> 11:43.925
Come on, go on.
I'm fine.

11:46.129 --> 11:48.045
All right.

11:53.636 --> 11:55.720
- Good night.
- Good night, baby.

12:12.622 --> 12:14.739
<i>I'll take Danny McGuire here.</i>

12:14.741 --> 12:16.908
<i>He knows the ropes. Don't you, Danny?</i>

12:16.910 --> 12:19.577
<i>Sure, I've had 'em</i>
<i>around my neck for years.</i>

12:23.583 --> 12:26.217
<i>- What?</i>
<i>- Oh, Miss Blodgett.</i>

12:26.219 --> 12:27.919
<i>Danny McGuire,</i>
<i>our new tenant.</i>

13:10.596 --> 13:14.015
<i>Oh, could you possibly
use me a picture, Mr. McGuire?</i>

13:14.017 --> 13:15.766
<i>Of course, I haven't had</i>
<i>much experience, but...</i>

13:21.391 --> 13:23.190
Boy, get up.
Time to go.

13:23.192 --> 13:26.560
We're going to Grandma's.
Okay, that's it, that's it.

13:26.562 --> 13:29.647
Here.

13:29.649 --> 13:31.899
Yeah.

13:31.901 --> 13:33.818
Come on.
Come on.

13:36.372 --> 13:38.572
Huh?

13:38.574 --> 13:41.826
<i>I'm gonna be
here three more years,</i>

13:41.828 --> 13:43.828
and you have to run
for reelection next year.

13:43.830 --> 13:45.329
And I promise you--

13:45.331 --> 13:47.548
this Parking Authority
stunt goes forward,

13:47.550 --> 13:50.418
we will primary you against
someone who can bury you.

13:50.420 --> 13:53.170
- Bring it.
- Nick, please, don't pick this fight.

13:53.172 --> 13:54.588
You barely got by
last year,

13:54.590 --> 13:55.840
and that was
before redistricting.

13:55.842 --> 13:57.842
Terry, don't throw
numbers at me, all right?

13:57.844 --> 14:00.261
I can run citywide,
and Jim knows it.

14:00.263 --> 14:03.147
<i>And if it wasn't for Martinelli
splitting the votes last year,</i>

14:03.149 --> 14:05.316
Pete Chema would be
sitting in that seat, not you.

14:05.318 --> 14:08.269
What'd you win with,
a kick-ass 36%?

14:08.271 --> 14:09.987
Shit.

14:12.492 --> 14:15.993
You want Bob Jean
off the Parking Authority?

14:15.995 --> 14:17.111
Fine.

14:17.113 --> 14:19.697
But there is
no way in hell

14:19.699 --> 14:21.532
that we can put John Zakian
back in there.

14:21.534 --> 14:24.251
Name a replacement we can live with,
and you got him.

14:26.622 --> 14:27.788
I don't know, Terry.

14:27.790 --> 14:29.840
I've really come
to like John Zakian.

14:38.384 --> 14:40.267
Damn!

14:49.395 --> 14:51.312
You messin'
with my head, girl.

14:54.233 --> 14:56.233
Damn, we got
the stairs, too, baby?

15:13.386 --> 15:15.803
Hey! No, no!

15:15.805 --> 15:17.755
Oh!

15:17.757 --> 15:18.973
<i>Hey!</i>

15:18.975 --> 15:21.642
Hey, come back here,
you motherfuckers!

15:26.766 --> 15:28.182
<i>Hey, yo!</i>

15:34.690 --> 15:39.443
Two guys, black,
20 or 25 years.

15:39.445 --> 15:41.245
Do you remember
what they were wearing?

15:41.247 --> 15:43.697
- Any distinguishing marks?
- It happened too fast.

15:43.699 --> 15:45.783
They were waiting for me
as I turned the corner.

15:45.785 --> 15:48.619
I-- I had just cashed my paycheck
at Getty Square,

15:48.621 --> 15:52.373
did some shopping, and then I
walked up here to visit my aunt.

15:52.375 --> 15:53.424
How much cash
did you have?

15:54.677 --> 15:57.511
$300 in an envelope
in my purse.

15:57.513 --> 15:59.880
You're just lucky
nothing worse happened to you.

15:59.882 --> 16:01.715
<i>I know.</i>

16:01.717 --> 16:05.019
I found this in a dumpster.
Yours?

16:05.021 --> 16:08.939
Anything else?
My packages?

16:08.941 --> 16:10.941
Nah, nothing like that.
Sorry.

16:10.943 --> 16:13.811
<i>Is this your place</i>
<i>of residence, miss?</i>

16:13.813 --> 16:16.230
No. I'm in
the townhouses now.

16:16.232 --> 16:17.982
I don't live here
anymore.

16:31.747 --> 16:32.963
Nay?

16:37.720 --> 16:39.086
I just heard.

16:39.088 --> 16:41.305
You happy now, Nick?

16:41.307 --> 16:43.557
Now that
I have no job?

16:43.559 --> 16:45.643
I'm gonna fix this.

16:45.645 --> 16:48.229
I'm gonna
fix this, okay?

16:48.231 --> 16:50.347
- I will.
- <i> How?</i>

16:50.349 --> 16:52.600
Bob Jean is telling
everyone he fired me

16:52.602 --> 16:55.352
because I'm incompetent.

16:55.354 --> 16:57.321
Jesus, Nick.

16:57.323 --> 16:59.657
<i>How am I gonna get another
job with that reputation?</i>

16:59.659 --> 17:00.658
I thought
I had the votes.

17:00.660 --> 17:02.109
I thought
I fucking had those votes.

17:02.111 --> 17:03.444
Nick Spano
thought so, too.

17:03.446 --> 17:06.196
He feels really bad about it,
you getting fired.

17:06.199 --> 17:09.333
Right.
Well, fuck it, you know?

17:10.786 --> 17:13.037
How could you
play politics with our lives?

17:16.041 --> 17:17.758
I'm so sorry.

17:18.877 --> 17:20.461
Yeah.

17:20.463 --> 17:22.680
I am.

17:30.690 --> 17:32.273
Okay, if there's
nothing else.

17:32.275 --> 17:33.891
Oh, I-- I got
something else.

17:33.893 --> 17:36.443
Someone needs to teach
our neighbors some manners.

17:36.445 --> 17:37.945
Yeah, they all
