36:56.588 --> 36:58.254
Thank you.

37:04.929 --> 37:06.763
<i>- Hey.</i>
- Hey.

37:06.765 --> 37:09.315
When are you gonna get
to the kitchen cabinets?

37:09.317 --> 37:11.234
They've been in boxes
for a month now already.

37:11.236 --> 37:13.069
- Yeah, yeah. It's on my list.
- Yeah, okay--

37:13.071 --> 37:15.071
Um, listen,
I'm gonna--

37:15.073 --> 37:17.440
I'm gonna
primary Vinni.

37:17.442 --> 37:18.524
Zaleski's
gonna back me.

37:18.526 --> 37:19.742
He's gonna put me
on the ticket

37:19.744 --> 37:23.162
and throw me enough cash
to mount the campaign, so...

37:23.164 --> 37:24.497
Great.

37:24.499 --> 37:25.748
You know, I can't--

37:25.750 --> 37:27.200
I can't run
in my own district,

37:27.202 --> 37:28.501
and I can't
sit this one out

37:28.503 --> 37:30.336
- if I want to run for mayor next time.
- <i> Mm-hmm.</i>

37:30.338 --> 37:33.039
So I don't really got
another choice.

37:33.041 --> 37:34.791
So you go
with Terry Zaleski,

37:34.793 --> 37:37.710
and you turn
against your friend?

37:37.712 --> 37:39.262
<i>You know what?</i>

37:39.264 --> 37:41.130
I'm gonna volunteer
for Vinni.

37:41.132 --> 37:42.799
<i>That's right.</i>

37:42.801 --> 37:45.518
I'm for Vinni Restiano
for council president.

37:45.520 --> 37:47.220
This is bullshit.

37:58.983 --> 38:00.066
Police! Freeze!

38:00.068 --> 38:01.651
- Hey!
- Oh! No!

38:01.653 --> 38:03.319
- Get off!
- That's the guy.

38:03.321 --> 38:04.403
- That's him!
- Get on the ground!

38:04.405 --> 38:06.122
She's on the third floor,
bleeding bad!

38:06.124 --> 38:07.957
- I didn't hurt nobody!
- Keep your mouth shut!

38:07.959 --> 38:09.625
Shut up!

38:10.912 --> 38:12.245
Is his name
on the lease?

38:12.247 --> 38:13.713
Oh, no, not
on the lease.

38:13.715 --> 38:15.331
Well, where
is he living, then?

38:15.333 --> 38:18.134
And why would he give this address?

38:35.019 --> 38:36.152
Hey.

38:36.154 --> 38:37.520
Hey, Vinni.

38:37.522 --> 38:39.822
What a fucking coward
you turned out to be, huh?

38:39.824 --> 38:42.024
- Hey, come on. - You couldn't
come in and tell me in person?

38:42.026 --> 38:44.360
You couldn't pick up the phone and
give me a call yourself, huh?

38:44.362 --> 38:46.362
It's not personal.
You know that. It's politics.

38:46.364 --> 38:49.248
Oh, please!
You and I both know that lie, remember?

38:49.250 --> 38:51.033
I don't have
any other options here.

38:51.035 --> 38:52.835
Me, neither, Nick.

38:52.837 --> 38:54.754
But don't think this is
gonna be easy for you.

38:54.756 --> 38:56.756
I got a little Yonkers
in me, too.

38:56.758 --> 38:59.125
- Vinni, come here, have a drink with me.
- No, you don't--

38:59.127 --> 39:03.629
I gotta know--
do you even believe in anything,

39:03.631 --> 39:06.716
anything other than
yourself?

39:08.686 --> 39:11.304
- Hmm?
- I'm sorry.

39:11.306 --> 39:13.389
Fuck you!

39:38.750 --> 39:41.834
The reason I'm running
is because of Mrs. Restiano's

39:41.836 --> 39:44.387
growing inability
to work with Mayor Zaleski.

39:44.389 --> 39:46.589
And, frankly,
I'm disillusioned.

39:46.591 --> 39:49.842
I have worked with the Republican
majority on the council

39:49.844 --> 39:53.596
to produce unanimous votes
92% of the time.

39:53.598 --> 39:56.766
Mrs. Restiano works only too well
with the Republican majority

39:56.768 --> 39:59.352
as an enemy
of our Democratic mayor.

39:59.354 --> 40:02.438
In fact, Nick and I
have voted the same way

40:02.440 --> 40:04.740
98% of the time,

40:04.742 --> 40:07.910
that is, until he decided
to run against me.

40:10.498 --> 40:13.532
Get over it, Nick.
People are on to you.

40:17.372 --> 40:20.840
The girl got her hearing notice
threatening eviction.

40:20.842 --> 40:22.625
City housing already
trying to throw her

40:22.627 --> 40:25.378
and her kids
out of doors.

40:25.380 --> 40:27.797
Well, if she lied
on her lease...

40:32.186 --> 40:33.803
We all lied.

40:35.857 --> 40:37.773
It's a game they rig up.

40:37.775 --> 40:40.693
If we have a man and he's
kicking in a little money for his kids,

40:40.695 --> 40:43.029
we gotta lie
so the rent doesn't go up

40:43.031 --> 40:44.146
or so we don't
get put out

40:44.148 --> 40:46.482
if ever he did anything wrong
once upon a time.

40:46.484 --> 40:50.069
- Yeah, but--
- She didn't cause the trouble,

40:50.071 --> 40:51.570
and her kids didn't,

40:51.572 --> 40:54.490
and the trouble didn't happen
anywhere near her home.

40:54.492 --> 40:56.208
But the whole
housing program's

40:56.210 --> 40:58.044
under fire
right now, Doreen,

40:58.046 --> 41:00.162
so they're gonna
make an example out of her.

41:00.164 --> 41:01.964
But he's the asshole
for using her address.

41:01.966 --> 41:03.666
But you know what?
She shouldn't have let him stay there

41:03.668 --> 41:05.384
if his name's
not on the lease.

41:05.386 --> 41:07.503
I'm sorry,
the stakes are too high.

41:07.505 --> 41:09.338
But he's her man.

41:09.340 --> 41:12.475
He fathered those kids.

41:12.477 --> 41:14.143
Look, people get busted,

41:14.145 --> 41:16.729
they use the men's shelter
as their address.

41:16.731 --> 41:19.315
There's a whole lot of men
in public housing,

41:19.317 --> 41:21.017
but not on the lease.

41:21.019 --> 41:24.320
- Well?
- <i> And not just men, either.</i>

41:24.322 --> 41:27.523
I mean,
my sister Gail lives with me.

41:29.944 --> 41:32.361
We lie,

41:32.363 --> 41:36.198
but they make these rules
as if we're children.

41:54.385 --> 41:55.885
I'm going to die
on that waiting list.

41:55.887 --> 41:57.636
Because that lady
was killed,

41:57.638 --> 41:59.605
I don't think they're ever gonna build
more townhouses now.

41:59.607 --> 42:01.223
Same as before--
yelling, protesting.

42:01.225 --> 42:02.975
I started looking
at apartment ads--

42:02.977 --> 42:04.310
three times as much
as Schlobohm

42:04.312 --> 42:06.562
and so filthy,
I wouldn't keep pigs there.

42:06.564 --> 42:08.197
<i>In the present situation,</i>

42:08.199 --> 42:10.199
<i>it's the citizens</i>
<i>of East Yonkers</i>

42:10.201 --> 42:12.785
<i>on whom we need to rely.</i>

42:12.787 --> 42:16.072
Because the reality is that
the budget constraints

42:16.074 --> 42:19.241
limit our ability to deploy
additional personnel

42:19.243 --> 42:21.243
<i>to resolve those issues.</i>

42:21.245 --> 42:23.796
Now, another point
that we need to discuss...

42:23.798 --> 42:25.798
- Excuse me, sir?
- ...with the homeowners--

42:25.800 --> 42:27.133
Excuse me, sir.

42:27.135 --> 42:29.085
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes, ma'am.

42:30.755 --> 42:32.421
My name
is Doreen Henderson.

42:32.423 --> 42:34.590
I represent
the Andrew Smith Townhouses

42:34.592 --> 42:37.476
on Gaffney Place
and Trenchard Street.

42:37.478 --> 42:39.228
I want to talk about
what I think

42:39.230 --> 42:41.397
a lot of people
are thinking about--

42:41.399 --> 42:44.483
the new townhouses and that lady
who was murdered across town.

42:44.485 --> 42:47.903
<i>The tenants are very upset</i>

42:47.905 --> 42:51.574
about what those two city councilmen
said last night on the TV

42:51.576 --> 42:53.826
about the kind
of people we are,

42:53.828 --> 42:56.779
and we're upset that they want
to screen people at the sites

42:56.781 --> 42:59.165
and check on who we have as
company and things like that.

42:59.167 --> 43:01.700
How would they like it if that
kind of thing was said about them?

43:01.702 --> 43:04.870
I'm sure they would be upset.

43:04.872 --> 43:08.791
The tenants
are decent people.

43:08.793 --> 43:11.794
And the tenant who might be evicted
because of this is, too.

43:13.264 --> 43:15.097
That man, Santos,
it shouldn't be assumed

43:15.099 --> 43:17.883
that he lived on Gaffney Place
just because he said so.

43:17.885 --> 43:19.852
Yes. Yes, ma'am. I--

43:21.355 --> 43:22.638
Yes, ma'am.

43:24.559 --> 43:27.526
I just wanted to say that as
commander of Second Precinct

43:27.528 --> 43:28.944
where most of
the townhouses are,

43:28.946 --> 43:30.946
we haven't really had
any unusual problems

43:30.948 --> 43:33.816
at any of the sites
or with the residents.

43:35.820 --> 43:37.620
<i>Thank you.</i>

43:37.622 --> 43:40.573
<i>Thank you, Captain, for your
assessment of the situation.</i>

43:40.575 --> 43:42.074
Is that one of yours, Bob?

43:42.076 --> 43:45.578
Lucille Lantz
had high hopes for her.

43:45.580 --> 43:47.329
She is proved right.

43:47.331 --> 43:50.916
<i>...we will of course
continue to offer protection</i>

43:50.918 --> 43:53.719
<i>and service</i>
<i>like we did before.</i>

43:53.721 --> 43:55.137
Miss Rowan, do you have
a statement to make

43:55.139 --> 43:56.889
before we hear testimony?

43:59.310 --> 44:01.644
Very well.

44:01.646 --> 44:03.729
We'll hear first
from Thomas Downer

44:03.731 --> 44:06.182
of the New York State
Division of Parole.

44:14.826 --> 44:17.743
Officer Downer,
you are John Santos's parole officer?

44:17.745 --> 44:18.994
Yes.

44:28.089 --> 44:30.005
How you been,
Billie?

44:31.125 --> 44:32.708
I'm Doreen.

44:32.710 --> 44:35.010
I remember you
from Schlobohm.

44:35.012 --> 44:37.463
Yeah, I live
around the way now.

44:37.465 --> 44:39.849
Good to get out
of Schlobohm, right?

44:41.135 --> 44:44.353
Got my eviction notice.

44:44.355 --> 44:46.605
Gotta get a new apartment,
I guess.

44:46.607 --> 44:50.059
Girl, listen, you can't
let them do this.

44:50.061 --> 44:51.894
Your man screwed you,

44:51.896 --> 44:54.730
but don't screw yourself double
by not fighting back.

44:57.235 --> 44:59.401
Billie, do you love
living here?

45:00.538 --> 45:03.372
Do your children
love living here?

45:07.245 --> 45:09.411
Come on.

45:09.413 --> 45:11.997
We gonna call
legal aid together.

45:28.432 --> 45:29.899
You voting today?

45:36.941 --> 45:38.691
Who you voting for?

45:38.693 --> 45:41.193
It's called a secret ballot
for a reason.

45:43.447 --> 45:44.947
Of course
I'm voting for you.

45:52.456 --> 45:53.539
Bye.

46:08.105 --> 46:11.023
- Hello?
- <i> Nay, it's Vinni.</i>

46:11.025 --> 46:13.642
Vinni, uh,
you just missed him.

46:13.644 --> 46:16.278
I'm-- I'm sorry
it's come to this.

46:16.280 --> 46:18.647
He betrayed me, Nay,

46:18.649 --> 46:20.532
and he's done
the same to you.

46:20.534 --> 46:22.952
<i>You need to know this.</i>

46:22.954 --> 46:25.821
He wasn't sleeping alone
on those trips to Albany.

46:27.408 --> 46:30.159
Ask him about
the Desmond Hotel.

46:30.161 --> 46:31.827
<i>I know</i>
<i>what happened there.</i>

46:46.010 --> 46:47.893
- It's sick.
- What?

46:47.895 --> 46:50.095
And wrong.

46:50.097 --> 46:51.680
Fuck him.

46:52.900 --> 46:54.600
Fuck him.

46:57.857 --> 47:01.493
_

47:15.006 --> 47:16.422
Miss O'Neal?

47:16.457 --> 47:18.957
It's me, Billie,
from 175.

47:19.010 --> 47:21.126
Sorry for walking
on your grass.

47:21.178 --> 47:22.628
It's nice grass,
too, right?

47:22.680 --> 47:24.380
How are ya?

47:24.382 --> 47:25.764
I'm okay.

47:25.800 --> 47:27.216
Listen, I don't mean
to bother you,

47:27.268 --> 47:29.635
but legal aid is trying to keep me
from being evicted.

47:29.687 --> 47:31.720
And it helps if I could get
some-- some neighbors

47:31.722 --> 47:34.056
to sign a petition
saying I wasn't a problem.

47:34.058 --> 47:35.974
Well, you're
not to me.

47:36.027 --> 47:38.644
Thank you,
Miss Norma.

47:38.696 --> 47:40.729
Oh, she can't...

47:40.731 --> 47:44.033
Let's go inside and sit
and do this right.

47:44.068 --> 47:47.569
I can come back. I mean, if
you have to be somewhere.

47:47.621 --> 47:49.738
Just to vote.
You voted yet?

47:49.790 --> 47:50.989
Uh, no.

47:51.042 --> 47:53.242
Habit with me.

47:53.294 --> 47:56.578
But I can't say
it seem to fix much.

47:56.580 --> 47:59.965
Likely to do more good today
signing your thing.

48:00.000 --> 48:01.667
Come on in the house,
though, baby.

48:01.719 --> 48:02.718
You need the keys.

48:02.753 --> 48:04.086
I wanna say
a special thank you

48:04.138 --> 48:06.722
for all of you who worked
so hard today out there

48:06.757 --> 48:09.925
manning the polls,
getting our message out.

48:11.479 --> 48:14.596
<i>Thank you all so much</i>
<i>for all...</i>

48:14.648 --> 48:17.149
I need another
fucking beer.

48:18.402 --> 48:20.652
<i>Thank you.</i>

48:20.688 --> 48:25.607
<i>This is a bit</i>
<i>of a bittersweet victory.</i>

48:25.609 --> 48:27.576
Nick...

48:27.611 --> 48:29.995
what happened
at the Desmond Hotel?

48:31.866 --> 48:34.950
The Desmond
in Albany?

48:36.504 --> 48:39.371
Nothing. Why? Was something
supposed to happen?

48:42.209 --> 48:43.959
Never mind.

48:43.961 --> 48:47.296
<i>...including Mayor Zaleski.</i>

48:47.298 --> 48:50.516
<i>It was a situation</i>
<i>that was unnecessary...</i>

48:50.551 --> 48:52.134
Yeah?

48:52.136 --> 48:54.803
<i>...and a situation that
should not be repeated again...</i>

48:54.889 --> 48:56.305
What are
the last wards left?

48:57.975 --> 48:59.808
<i>And now the results...</i>

48:59.860 --> 49:00.976
Yeah, thanks.

49:01.028 --> 49:04.363
<i>Tonight I intend to ask</i>
<i>for the resignation</i>

49:04.398 --> 49:06.448
<i>of the Yonkers</i>
<i>Democratic Party.</i>

49:08.452 --> 49:10.786
Well, you gave it
a run, Nick.

49:10.821 --> 49:12.488
Vinni was the incumbent,
but you--

49:14.375 --> 49:15.574
You gave it
a good shot.

49:15.626 --> 49:17.459
Got close.

49:17.495 --> 49:19.628
Yeah.

49:19.663 --> 49:22.381
Well, that's
twice in a row

49:22.416 --> 49:23.749
I've lost
running citywide,

49:23.801 --> 49:25.134
so by the rules
of the game,

49:25.169 --> 49:26.969
I'm done as a candidate.

49:30.641 --> 49:33.509
So, what do you have for me
in the administration?

49:41.435 --> 49:43.185
Jim...

49:44.188 --> 49:46.071
promises were made.

49:46.106 --> 49:48.607
Promises?

49:54.198 --> 49:57.449
You're just gonna,
you know,

49:57.501 --> 49:59.868
just use me up
like that?

49:59.870 --> 50:00.919
You gonna run me
against Vinni,

50:00.955 --> 50:02.371
and that way you get rid
of one of us, right?

50:02.373 --> 50:05.424
Okay.
Well...

50:05.459 --> 50:07.676
Hey, and don't think
I didn't see that, um--

50:07.711 --> 50:11.547
that, uh, report
in "The Herald Statesman" yesterday.

50:11.549 --> 50:14.099
That investigation
of the IDA you guys are doing,

50:14.134 --> 50:15.801
that secretary
that stole some money?

50:15.853 --> 50:18.604
- What about it?
- That's the last bullet, right?

50:18.639 --> 50:20.138
Wh-what do you mean?

50:20.191 --> 50:24.643
As mayor,
I was chairman of the IDA, Jim.

50:24.695 --> 50:27.729
But I didn't steal shit. You look at
my bank account, I didn't steal anything.

50:27.781 --> 50:31.233
- Then don't worry-- - Yeah, but I'm
still gonna get investigated anyway?

50:31.235 --> 50:34.286
If I'd have beat Vinni, you would've
come at me with that bullshit anyway.

50:34.321 --> 50:37.122
I get Vinni for you,
but then you get me, is that right?

50:37.157 --> 50:38.457
- Nick...
- Huh?

50:38.492 --> 50:41.827
I don't have a pot
to piss in, Jim!

50:41.879 --> 50:43.495
I didn't steal,
but you wanna take

50:43.547 --> 50:44.746
what's left
of my reputation?

50:44.748 --> 50:46.248
You wanna tear
that down as well?

50:46.300 --> 50:48.217
- Nick, you need to calm down, okay?
- Fuck you, Jim!

50:48.252 --> 50:51.053
And you tell Zaleski
I said fuck him, too!

50:51.088 --> 50:53.055
Piece of shit.

50:56.477 --> 50:58.093
We work
for trucks.

50:58.095 --> 51:00.729
Yeah, we work
for garbage trucks.

51:00.764 --> 51:04.733
Let's clean up
so everybody can get this dirt away.

51:08.772 --> 51:09.771
Poodle Lady.

51:09.773 --> 51:11.773
<i>Poodle Lady.</i>

51:17.748 --> 51:20.115
<i>My name is Jaron.</i>

51:20.117 --> 51:22.284
What's their names?

51:26.290 --> 51:30.208
Martini, Brandy,
and Alexander.

51:35.549 --> 51:37.549
Do you like dogs?

51:38.552 --> 51:39.801
Yes.

51:39.803 --> 51:41.637
- Soft, isn't he?
- Yes.

51:41.689 --> 51:44.890
<i>Yeah. Somebody's
playing behind you here.</i>

51:44.942 --> 51:46.725
He's really excited.

51:46.777 --> 51:47.943
<i>22 up!</i>

51:47.978 --> 51:49.444
<i>AC plain</i>
<i>and a full house.</i>

51:49.480 --> 51:52.531
You should have
gotten a haircut.

51:52.566 --> 51:55.117
You should have
taken off of work.

51:55.152 --> 51:56.868
Seriously.

51:56.904 --> 51:58.654
I think you would
look much better

51:58.706 --> 52:00.822
with shorter hair.

52:00.824 --> 52:02.658
I think you'd look better
without eyebrows.

52:04.328 --> 52:06.995
I can't do that.
I can't take them out.

52:08.632 --> 52:11.500
As it so happens, I made
an appointment for tomorrow.

52:11.502 --> 52:14.753
- For your hair?
- Mm-hmm.

52:14.805 --> 52:17.422
- That's good.
- Mm-hmm.

52:17.474 --> 52:20.392
Oh, God, it's almost 2:00.
You gotta get me back.

52:20.427 --> 52:22.728
- No, I'll be in trouble.
- Play hooky with me.

52:22.763 --> 52:24.763
- I can't.
- Come on.

52:24.815 --> 52:26.815
I can't, and you
are going to go back

52:26.850 --> 52:30.268
and help your brother
with the cabinets today.

52:30.321 --> 52:31.687
Okay.

52:33.273 --> 52:35.357
What's that face?

52:39.413 --> 52:42.581
- It's just...
- Nothing from Surdoval?

52:44.251 --> 52:46.118
No, no, no.
There's nothing for me there.

52:46.170 --> 52:47.619
They made that
very clear.

52:47.671 --> 52:48.870
Well, screw them.

52:48.922 --> 52:50.539
Seriously.
Screw them.

52:50.541 --> 52:52.791
You can teach,
you can practice law,

52:52.843 --> 52:56.345
you can do whatever
the fuck you want now.

52:56.380 --> 52:58.547
Yeah. Screw them.

52:58.549 --> 53:00.048
Yeah.

53:01.935 --> 53:03.602
Let's go.
It's late.

53:03.637 --> 53:06.054
Is your stomach better?

53:06.056 --> 53:07.973
Yeah, it's okay.

53:08.025 --> 53:11.109
Okay.

53:16.900 --> 53:18.567
Bye, thank you.

53:20.237 --> 53:22.487
- Hey, Nay. Nay.
- What?

53:22.489 --> 53:24.122
This, uh--
this IDA thing,

53:24.124 --> 53:25.824
- they're gunning for me.
- No.

53:25.826 --> 53:27.492
Listen, Zaleski,
Surdoval,

53:27.494 --> 53:29.578
they've got Maniglia
and these other creeps digging into it,

53:29.580 --> 53:31.880
- like everyone's corrupt except for them.
- Nick...

53:33.751 --> 53:37.219
- Who cares what they think?
- I care. I care. It's my reputation.

53:37.221 --> 53:39.254
You haven't done anything wrong.
You're innocent.

53:39.256 --> 53:41.723
